  "text": "is a 2D extension of the classical KdV equation which does not admit localized solitons. However, the solitons q c (t, x) = Q c (x − ct − σ) of KdV, defined above (Q c + Q 2 c = cQ c ) provide traveling waves solutions of KP-II independent of y, called line-solitons. It is a classical question to study the stability and asymptotic stability of these line-solitons with respect to localized (or periodic) perturbations. The problem was recently settled in [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . For a > 0, define the weighted norm · La by",
